title: For Sale:  Chilean 1895 7x57mm long rifle
postcontent:
I have for sale a Chilean 1895 7x57mm long rifle. This rifle is in excellent condition for it’s age. The rifle sports many charcoal and straw colored part as well as deep rich bluing (nearly 95%). This bore looks like it is new mirror like finish. Comes with the cleaning rod. 

Now the bad news, Bubba decided to take a matching near mint 1895 Chilean and tried make a target shooter out of it. He installed a 12x Unterl target scope. This consisted of drilling and tapping two (2) screws in the front ring (professional done and did not penetrate to the barrel shank. He then removed the rear sight and handguard and D&T two (2) holes into to the rear sight base. 

He next had the matching bolt bent over and ground down (very thin to clear the scope). All in all, kiss an all matching 1895 Chilean long rifle good bye. 

Fortunately, Bubba saved the parts and I found a matching bolt (numbers match the bolt parts not the rifle). He still had the handguard, rear sight ladder, spring and screw. 

I bought this to use as a shooter, but have come across others over so time for this one to go. 

This is not a mint all matching rifle that could cost $600-900. But a really nice Chilean 1895 shooter. Better than the usual grey metal, oily black stock mismatched beater. Not many left to choose from. 

Asking $295. Might trade for a nice Yugo 24/52c 8mm rifle (Yugo captured VZ-24). 

I can take more detailed pics if requested. Pick up in the east valley. Pick up in the east valley. For sale to legal Arizona residents. No out of state sales. 

Thanks for looking

Miami Shooters Club provides such a course with its team of NRA certified instructors - who will teach students the important fundamentals of how to safely use a semi-automatic pistol and revolver. Your concealed weapons permit will allow you to concealed carry in more than 30 states.

Miami Shooters Club's instructors carry multiple certifications under the NRA, have traveled abroad to train and receive firearm certifications, and are hand-to-hand self defense experts - having taught multiple seminars for the Miami Dade Police Department. Under their instruction in the concealed carry class, students will learn the mechanisms behind pistols and how they operate while learning how to grip the firearm, aim, pull the trigger, get into a proper stance, and much more. The class also covers many of the legal issues and expected ethics of concealed carry in Florida. The classes are designed for complete beginners who have never touched a gun before... but experienced shooters will learn something as well.

At the end of the classroom portion, students will safely discharge a pistol under the supervision of a certified instructor, as required by the State of Florida. Miami Shooters Club will provide a firearm, ammunition, eye protection, and ear protection at no extra cost.

title: For Sale:  Arsenal SGL-107CR AK47 Pattern Rifle
postcontent:
Up for sale is "like new" Arsenal SGL-107CR AK pattern rifle chambered in 7.62x39.  This is considered by many as the best AK you can buy with going the expensive custom route. Speaking of custom rifles Kreb's Customs and Rifle Dynamics, the two best AK shops in the country, start with Arsenal made rifles due to their top notch quality.

This rifle features a 16.25" Bulgarian made chrome lined, cold hammer forged barrel which is considered the best AK barrel in the world, not an American made barrel like many of the other AKs being made one US. The muzzle thread are 24mm.  The Rifle also features the desirable side folding polymer stock. The stock has an indention so when folded it fits over the left hand scope rail mounted on the reciever. The lockup of the folding stock is unlike any of the others I have felt as it is rock solid. The rifle has an Arsenal 2 stage trigger that is probably the nicest AK trigger I have felt. It also has the high quality polymer handguards that have a stainless steel best shield that does not allow the handguard to heat up like traditional wood ones.  The action is very smooth with no hang up or resistance like other cheaper AKs. The rifle also has the rare 90 degree gas block with special gas port tuning and integrated front sight. The rifle will come with 2 Magpul 30 round PMags.

This model of rifle is very hard to get ahold of since it is made to become a Short Barreled Rifle with the correct paperwork, or you can shoot it as is with great accuracy.  I am asking $1200 which is fair number considering you can't find these anywhere and they are not being imported anymore by Arsenal, but I am to offers. I would consider trading for an arsenal sgl107fr or sgl21. You can reach me by email or texting me at 724seven146020. Thanks for viewing.
